<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Does anyone have any idea whether range (any range inside maximum range, I mean) has any effect on either accuracy or damage or missile weapons? And whether Archery or <a class="nonexistent" href="./FooMastery">FooMastery</a> skill has any effect on that range. Thanks!  <p>
Edit: Ahhh... Killerbunnies to the rescue again. It modifies to-hit... D is the distance to the monster... <a class="external" href=".killerbunnies.org/angband/skill-220.html#abil_bow"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">http://killerbunnies.org/angband/skill-220.html#abil_bow</a>... Well that answers ONE question. The other question is whether it affects damage and whether Foomastery affects range outside of affecting the Ability score...  
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: The maximum range is 10 + 5*M, where M is the final multiplier of the weapon (base multiplier + extra might). You can obtain a bonus of +3 to the extra might multiplier with the foo_mastery skill (i.e. increase the range by +15). The range does not affect damage. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: So the theoretical limit on range with a non-magic Heavy XBow would be 45. A second, related question is what the absolute limit on perception is. Could you (theoretically) fire a bolt outside of your visual range? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Yes. You can try this in the plains. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Here's a somewhat associated question: Does the blast radius on exploding ammos vary at all? Either per char level, distance fired, or ammo type? (And the second, idea-type question: <em>Should</em> it?)) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: The base damage of an exploding ammo is twice the damage of the ammunition (e.g. an exploding Arrow (1d4) (+0,+0) has a base damage of 2d4).  The blast radius and the damage of the exploding ammunition depends only on the specific type. Light ammo (e.g. pebbles) deal half this amount in a radius 2 zone, normal ammo (e.g. arrows, bolts, iron shots) the base damage in a radius 3 zone, heavy ammo (e.g. seeker arrows and bolts, mithril shots) twice this damage in a radius 4 zone. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a>: Ermmm... what about piercing?  What's that effect on damage (piercing)? And what does ricochet do (in terms of damage)? 
</p>
